00:36:18.301 --> 00:36:21.179
- Oh. look. Kendra. I...
- You think our bougie son

733
00:36:21.262 --> 00:36:23.598
has no right to associate
with other black kids

734
00:36:23.681 --> 00:36:26.142
without stamping a presumption of guilt
all over himself?

735
00:36:27.018 --> 00:36:30.938
No. I think our half-white. half-black.
who-gives-a-shit-what-race-he-is son...

736
00:36:31.522 --> 00:36:34.650
The one who got 1470 on his SATs
and aced AP Physics.

737
00:36:34.734 --> 00:36:36.861
knows better than to commit
unforced errors in life

738
00:36:36.944 --> 00:36:38.196
by taking stupid risks.

739
00:36:39.113 --> 00:36:41.657
Especially. when he is on the cusp
of doing great things.

740
00:36:41.741 --> 00:36:44.493
I think he understands that.
like it or not.

741
00:36:45.203 --> 00:36:47.830
the way that you present yourself in life
has consequences.

742
00:36:47.914 --> 00:36:50.541
If you wear your pants
halfway down your ass

743
00:36:50.625 --> 00:36:52.501
and ghetto hair. then you got...

744
00:36:52.585 --> 00:36:54.545
Then you got no right to complain
when you walk by

745
00:36:54.587 --> 00:36:56.505
and a white lady clutches her purse?

746
00:36:57.048 --> 00:36:59.217
You got no right to complain
when you walk by

747
00:36:59.300 --> 00:37:00.843
and <i>any </i>lady clutches her purse.

748
00:37:00.927 --> 00:37:02.929
No. No. no. no. no. no. That is not... No.

749
00:37:03.012 --> 00:37:05.765
You are saying that associating
with other black kids

750
00:37:05.848 --> 00:37:07.266
is taking a stupid risk.

751
00:37:07.350 --> 00:37:09.190
Oh. come on. Kenny.
that's not what I'm saying.

752
00:37:09.227 --> 00:37:10.495
- Let me ask you.
- You know that!

753
00:37:10.519 --> 00:37:12.831
If this little asshole had told you
that Jamal was in a car

754
00:37:12.855 --> 00:37:15.983
with two white boys he barely knew.
would you be blaming him then?

755
00:37:16.067 --> 00:37:17.652
Would that be an unforced error?

756
00:37:17.735 --> 00:37:19.415
If I didn't know 'em. if I hadn't met 'em.

757
00:37:19.445 --> 00:37:21.447
black or white.
you're damn right. it would be.

758
00:37:21.530 --> 00:37:22.740
Scott...

759
00:37:23.241 --> 00:37:26.077
no matter how many privileges he's got.

760
00:37:26.619 --> 00:37:29.872
the world still looks at him
like it looks at me.

761
00:37:30.748 --> 00:37:31.582
not you.

762
00:37:31.666 --> 00:37:32.666
Oh. boy.

763
00:37:33.251 --> 00:37:35.419
I tell you.
I can see exactly what's been going on.

764
00:37:35.503 --> 00:37:38.172
I'm out of the house a few months.
and sure enough.

765
00:37:38.256 --> 00:37:39.382
you are filling his mind

766
00:37:39.465 --> 00:37:41.509
full of victimhood psychobabble.

767
00:37:41.592 --> 00:37:43.761
- Oh. you know what?
- "Pity me! Pity me!"

768
00:37:43.844 --> 00:37:45.530
- I've done nothing of the sort.
- Yeah.

769
00:37:45.554 --> 00:37:47.056
Instead of pointing a finger at me.

770
00:37:47.139 --> 00:37:49.308
maybe you ought to be looking
in the mirror.

771
00:37:49.392 --> 00:37:50.476
Oh. this is my fault now?

772
00:37:50.559 --> 00:37:54.188
Well. you're the one who disappeared
at the pivotal moment in his life.

773
00:37:54.272 --> 00:37:55.314
Excuse me?

774
00:37:55.398 --> 00:37:57.275
You know exactly what I'm saying.

775
00:37:57.358 --> 00:37:59.819
I coached his baseball team for ten years.

776
00:37:59.902 --> 00:38:02.321
- Mmm.
- I went to every one of his concerts.

777
00:38:02.405 --> 00:38:03.990
Have I ever missed a banquet

778
00:38:04.073 --> 00:38:05.491
or a game or an event or a meet?

779
00:38:05.574 --> 00:38:08.136
- That's not what I'm talking about.
- What are you talking about?

780
00:38:08.160 --> 00:38:09.620
You walked out on him.

781
00:38:13.874 --> 00:38:14.792
I did not.

782
00:38:14.875 --> 00:38:16.294
- Yes. you did.
- Bullshit.

783
00:38:16.377 --> 00:38:17.420
- You did.
- No. I didn't.

784
00:38:17.503 --> 00:38:19.463
I'm sorry. but that is exactly what you...

785
00:38:19.547 --> 00:38:20.899
- You know what?
- You did!

786
00:38:20.923 --> 00:38:22.133
You up and walked out on him.

787
00:38:22.216 --> 00:38:24.427
I didn't walk out on him.
I walked out on you.

788
00:38:31.517 --> 00:38:32.517
Oh.

789
00:38:32.935 --> 00:38:35.021
I didn't mean for it
to come out like that.

790
00:38:46.991 --> 00:38:47.991
I just...

791
00:38:48.784 --> 00:38:52.163
I'm so sick and tired of having
the same frickin' argument with you

792
00:38:52.246 --> 00:38:55.624
over and over and over again.
That is what I walked away from. Not...

793
00:38:56.751 --> 00:38:57.751
You know.

794
00:39:01.797 --> 00:39:03.758
Shit. Kenny. I'm sorry.

795
00:39:03.841 --> 00:39:05.092
- Stop.
- I didn't mean to...

796
00:39:05.176 --> 00:39:07.261
Just put the shovel down
and stop digging.

797
00:39:07.345 --> 00:39:10.473
Listen. J is on his way to being
a commissioned officer

798
00:39:10.556 --> 00:39:12.975
at one of the most elite institutions
on Earth.

799
00:39:13.059 --> 00:39:14.143
My job is done.

800
00:39:14.226 --> 00:39:15.644
He is a man now.

801
00:39:16.103 --> 00:39:17.355
A man I am so proud of.

802
00:39:17.438 --> 00:39:18.272
I know.

803
00:39:18.356 --> 00:39:22.610
So I cannot... I cannot have you telling me
I didn't do my job as a father.

804
00:39:23.110 --> 00:39:24.110
Okay.

805
00:39:26.864 --> 00:39:28.824
- I am not your father. Kendra.
- Okay.

806
00:39:28.908 --> 00:39:30.951
- That's what walking out looks like.
- All right.

807
00:39:31.035 --> 00:39:32.119
- So don't. Don't.
- Scott.

808
00:39:32.203 --> 00:39:33.954
- Please. Please.
- I said I get it.

809
00:39:56.727 --> 00:39:57.727
Hey.

810
00:39:59.313 --> 00:40:00.648
Kenny.

811
00:40:04.276 --> 00:40:06.070
Everything's gonna be fine. all right?

812
00:40:06.153 --> 00:40:08.114
Let's just try and relax.

813
00:40:14.578 --> 00:40:17.748
This time of night. I always get agitated.

814
00:40:19.583 --> 00:40:21.585
You have no idea.

815
00:40:22.545 --> 00:40:25.464
I'm usually awake about this time.

816
00:40:25.548 --> 00:40:29.051
I don't know I've had a sleep-filled night
since that boy was born.

817
00:40:35.808 --> 00:40:39.937
<i>Most nights. my eyes fire wide open
out of a sound sleep.</i>

818
00:40:40.354 --> 00:40:44.358
<i>Heart beating so hard
I feel it throbbing in my ears.</i>

819
00:40:44.733 --> 00:40:46.694
<i>Always right about this time.</i>

820
00:40:49.822 --> 00:40:52.032
<i>Too late to go back to sleep...</i>

821
00:40:53.951 --> 00:40:55.995
<i>too early to get on with the day.</i>

822
00:41:00.499 --> 00:41:05.004
<i>You... just snoring away.</i>

823
00:41:11.969 --> 00:41:15.097
Usually. I go stand
in the door to his room...

824
00:41:18.142 --> 00:41:20.102
<i>and listen to him breathe.</i>

825
00:41:22.980 --> 00:41:28.277
Sometimes I go in and...
touch the muscle on his neck.

826
00:41:30.863 --> 00:41:32.239
Or shoulder.

827
00:41:34.533 --> 00:41:36.744
<i>Stand there and bullshit myself.</i>

828
00:41:36.827 --> 00:41:41.832
<i>"Don't worry. Kendra.
he is big and powerful.</i>

829
00:41:41.916 --> 00:41:43.375
This world can't hurt him."

830
00:41:46.045 --> 00:41:51.425
Until that nagging feeling comes back.
and I dwell on how fragile he is.

831
00:41:53.427 --> 00:41:56.263
<i>And whatever nightmare
that has just woke me up.</i>

832
00:41:56.347 --> 00:42:01.101
<i>someone texting in an SUV
or an errant punch in a bar fight.</i>

833
00:42:01.477 --> 00:42:03.479
<i>a ruptured appendix</i>

834
00:42:03.562 --> 00:42:06.232
in some third world country. Most...

835
00:42:06.315 --> 00:42:09.610
Most mothers can sit there in the dark
and get rational.

836
00:42:09.693 --> 00:42:10.736
go back to sleep.

837
00:42:10.819 --> 00:42:15.908
But sometimes. in my nightmares.
I see nooses and crosses

838
00:42:15.991 --> 00:42:19.286
and white men with Brylcreem crew cuts.

839
00:42:33.092 --> 00:42:37.846
Last summer... when Jamal
wanted to drive with Jeff to Bonnaroo.

840
00:42:37.930 --> 00:42:41.725
- I was... I just...
- No. look. J and I just thought

841
00:42:41.809 --> 00:42:44.037
you were a little over-the-top
with the mother hen thing.

842
00:42:44.061 --> 00:42:45.354
thinking he was too young.

843
00:42:45.437 --> 00:42:47.415
- Too young?
- We disagreed and we moved on.

844
00:42:47.439 --> 00:42:49.119
Too young
had nothing to do with that shit.

845
00:42:49.191 --> 00:42:52.570
My granddaddy was fighting in Okinawa
when he was 17.

846
00:42:52.653 --> 00:42:53.862
Too <i>young?</i>

847
00:42:56.323 --> 00:42:57.449
It wasn't that.

848
00:42:58.742 --> 00:43:04.206
It was the prospect of him
driving through the Deep South.

849
00:43:06.041 --> 00:43:09.712
My son. alone with a white boy

850
00:43:09.795 --> 00:43:12.965
driving Sherman's March to the Sea
in reverse.

851
00:43:15.551 --> 00:43:19.763
Maybe he and Jeff stopped
to get gas in some little town

852
00:43:19.847 --> 00:43:21.432
'cause he doesn't know any better

853
00:43:21.515 --> 00:43:25.227
because we raised him to believe
that the world is full...

854
00:43:26.395 --> 00:43:27.855
full of goodness.

855
00:43:30.566 --> 00:43:35.279
And he starts batting his doe eyes
at some cute little white girl.

856
00:43:38.115 --> 00:43:40.534
Maybe the two of them walk
into a burger joint.

857
00:43:40.993 --> 00:43:43.203
happens to be an alt-right hangout.

858
00:43:46.665 --> 00:43:52.004
Maybe... some guy with a swastika
tattooed to his biceps

859
00:43:52.087 --> 00:43:54.298
had a little too much to drink. and...

860
00:43:55.883 --> 00:43:58.927
doesn't like the look...
of this boy

861
00:43:59.011 --> 00:44:02.389
who's poisoning
the country's racial purity.

862
00:44:03.307 --> 00:44:06.518
But the worst one.
the one that always comes back.

863
00:44:06.602 --> 00:44:10.439
is I see him getting stopped by a cop
for doing nothing in particular.

864
00:44:10.522 --> 00:44:13.192
<i>And I see ankle-high boots and...</i>

865
00:44:15.027 --> 00:44:16.070
badges...

866
00:44:19.073 --> 00:44:21.033
<i>and nightsticks.</i>

867
00:44:25.829 --> 00:44:28.332
And I think back on that night I was...

868
00:44:30.584 --> 00:44:32.294
five years old...

869
00:44:32.378 --> 00:44:36.632
and watched
my stoic mother doubled over.

870
00:44:37.174 --> 00:44:38.926
sobbing in the kitchen

871
00:44:39.009 --> 00:44:42.137
because Arthur McDuffie
had been beaten to death by the cops...

872
00:44:42.221 --> 00:44:44.682
...and they'd acquitted those cops.

873
00:44:49.061 --> 00:44:54.441
And you... were a little boy
asleep on the other side of town.

874
00:44:54.525 --> 00:44:56.819
dreaming of becoming one.

875
00:45:00.322 --> 00:45:01.949
I'm scared.

876
00:45:02.032 --> 00:45:03.200
Don't be scared.

877
00:45:03.283 --> 00:45:04.118
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

878
00:45:04.201 --> 00:45:05.681
This is just some frivolous nonsense.

879
00:45:05.744 --> 00:45:07.624
They probably had
the music cranked up too loud.

880
00:45:07.705 --> 00:45:09.915
- You think?
- Yeah. you know how he likes to do.

881
00:45:12.626 --> 00:45:15.337
Or his buddies had a couple of beers
in the back seat. stupid shit.

882
00:45:15.421 --> 00:45:17.172
kids sowing wild oats.

883
00:45:19.800 --> 00:45:22.928
But let's not piss these people off. okay?

884
00:45:25.055 --> 00:45:26.055
Let's just...

885
00:45:27.266 --> 00:45:28.308
keep calm.

886
00:45:29.226 --> 00:45:31.770
Half an hour.
the three of us will be at Denny's...

887
00:45:33.605 --> 00:45:35.566
having a teachable moment.

888
00:45:42.030 --> 00:45:43.991
Have you talked to him recently?

889
00:45:44.450 --> 00:45:45.576
I talk to him every day.

890
00:45:45.659 --> 00:45:47.369
- Texting mostly. but...
- No.

891
00:45:47.453 --> 00:45:51.165
I mean. have you talked to him about...

892
00:45:51.248 --> 00:45:52.291
About what?

893
00:45:53.333 --> 00:45:54.376
West Point.

894
00:45:55.627 --> 00:45:56.628
What about it?

895
00:45:57.254 --> 00:45:59.894
- I don't wanna get in the middle of this.
- What about it?

896
00:46:01.550 --> 00:46:03.135
- Well. he's...
- He's what?

897
00:46:03.218 --> 00:46:04.803
He's rethinking it.

898
00:46:06.388 --> 00:46:07.806
He's rethinking what?

899
00:46:10.017 --> 00:46:11.393
You should talk to him.

900
00:46:11.477 --> 00:46:12.770
About what. Kendra?

901
00:46:15.230 --> 00:46:17.983
He's thinking about taking
the farm team contract.

902
00:46:18.817 --> 00:46:20.903
Or maybe seeing
where the guitar thing might go.

903
00:46:20.986 --> 00:46:21.987
Really?

904
00:46:22.070 --> 00:46:23.697
- Listen...
- Jesus Christ. Kenny. Again?

905
00:46:23.781 --> 00:46:26.092
It'd probably just be a deferment.
He's afraid to tell you.

906
00:46:26.116 --> 00:46:27.409
Yeah. well. he should be.

907
00:46:30.579 --> 00:46:31.747
I hope this wasn't your idea.

908
00:46:31.830 --> 00:46:33.791
- Okay. look.
- Are you encouraging this nonsense?

909
00:46:33.874 --> 00:46:36.335
He doesn't have the arm speed
to make it out of Double-A ball.

910
00:46:36.418 --> 00:46:37.961
He doesn't have the talent.

911
00:46:40.464 --> 00:46:42.716
A brutal reckoning that I. his father.

912
00:46:43.175 --> 00:46:45.385
not you. got to make with him. thank you.

913
00:46:45.469 --> 00:46:46.678
And the guitar?

914
00:46:47.346 --> 00:46:49.848
He's gonna. what?
Play the guitar. like. for a living?

915
00:46:49.932 --> 00:46:52.100
Just because you were too scared
to pursue your dreams.

916
00:46:52.184 --> 00:46:53.745
- don't take it out on him.
- Oh. please.

917
00:46:53.769 --> 00:46:54.929
Let him try while he's young.

918
00:46:55.562 --> 00:46:58.190
At worst.
he spends some time finding himself.

919
00:46:58.273 --> 00:47:00.313
Oh. sure.
You kick around trying to "find yourself."

920
00:47:00.359 --> 00:47:02.444
and before you know it.
you're a 40-year-old dude

921
00:47:02.528 --> 00:47:05.572
with a 150 IQ and no college degree.

922
00:47:07.115 --> 00:47:11.370
Then you're making. what. 450 a week
in a goddamn wedding cover band.

923
00:47:12.329 --> 00:47:13.831
Being hired by a guy

924
00:47:13.914 --> 00:47:16.124
who can afford to drop $100K
on the wedding

925
00:47:16.208 --> 00:47:18.252
because he didn't waste
ten years of his life

926
00:47:18.335 --> 00:47:20.879
pursuing his dreams of. you know.
the Olympic curling team.

927
00:47:20.963 --> 00:47:23.048
or writing the next great American novel.

928
00:47:23.131 --> 00:47:25.193
- That's not what I meant.
- The men in my family have

929
00:47:25.217 --> 00:47:27.469
served this country every generation
since they got here.

930
00:47:27.553 --> 00:47:29.304
He is not entitled
to break that tradition.

931
00:47:29.388 --> 00:47:30.639
- Scott.
- It's not an option.

932
00:47:30.722 --> 00:47:32.307
End of discussion.

933
00:47:32.391 --> 00:47:33.725
Sorry to interrupt.

934
00:47:34.101 --> 00:47:36.019
Coffee. No cream. no sugar.

935
00:47:36.103 --> 00:47:37.663
Thanks.

936
00:47:37.729 --> 00:47:39.940
So. I got some more information for you.

937
00:47:40.023 --> 00:47:41.023
It's not a lot.

938
00:47:41.775 --> 00:47:43.777
I checked the computer intake log again.

939
00:47:46.655 --> 00:47:50.200
Your son was identified
as a vehicle occupant

940
00:47:50.284 --> 00:47:52.119
in a traffic stop in your Lexus.

941
00:47:52.202 --> 00:47:55.956
I also confirmed there were
two other black males

942
00:47:56.039 --> 00:47:57.833
in the vehicle when it was stopped.

943
00:47:57.916 --> 00:47:59.042
Why were they stopped?

944
00:47:59.126 --> 00:48:00.669
The log's not really that specific.

945
00:48:00.752 --> 00:48:02.713
The general "infraction" category
was checked off.

946
00:48:02.796 --> 00:48:04.047
What does that mean?

947
00:48:04.756 --> 00:48:06.967
It's just whatever
the patrol officer logged in

948
00:48:07.050 --> 00:48:09.177
from his laptop in the patrol car.

949
00:48:09.261 --> 00:48:10.470
He. like. checks off a box.

950
00:48:10.554 --> 00:48:11.930
So this tells us nothing.

951
00:48:12.014 --> 00:48:15.058
Well. it's not showing up
as a pursuit following felony.

952
00:48:15.434 --> 00:48:17.728
a stolen car. BOLO.
You know. the really bad stuff...

953
00:48:17.811 --> 00:48:19.271
- Okay.
- ...you can check off.

954
00:48:19.354 --> 00:48:22.608
- Who were the other boys?
- Yeah. I'm not allowed to. um...

955
00:48:25.444 --> 00:48:28.113
Okay. this stays between us.
Badge to badge.

956
00:48:31.033 --> 00:48:33.994
DaShawn Rolle and Jarvis Bell.

957
00:48:34.077 --> 00:48:35.077
You know them?

958
00:48:35.871 --> 00:48:38.665
Uh. Bell is a 20-year-old
with misdemeanor convictions.

959
00:48:38.749 --> 00:48:39.875
He had an open warrant.

960
00:48:39.958 --> 00:48:41.418
- For what?
- That I cannot tell you.

961
00:48:41.501 --> 00:48:43.295
You see. Ken? Do you see what I'm saying?

962
00:48:43.378 --> 00:48:45.213
Um. one other thing.

963
00:48:45.297 --> 00:48:47.925
I gave your son's social media accounts
a quick look over.

964
00:48:48.008 --> 00:48:51.470
Really? That's what you've been doing
while we're standing around in here?

965
00:48:51.553 --> 00:48:54.640
Social media is. like. the first stop
in missing persons cases.

966
00:48:54.723 --> 00:48:55.723
- Oh. please.
- Fact!

967
00:48:59.019 --> 00:49:01.480
And that I did learn in a training video.

968
00:49:05.776 --> 00:49:08.445
Your son posted something on Instagram.

969
00:49:08.862 --> 00:49:12.199
A photo of a bumper sticker
on the back of your Lexus.

970
00:49:14.076 --> 00:49:18.789
"Shoot cops with your camera phone
whenever they make a bust."

971
00:49:19.581 --> 00:49:21.333
- Excuse me?
- That is what it says.

972
00:49:21.416 --> 00:49:23.043
- "Shoot cops"?
- Yeah. yeah.

973
00:49:23.126 --> 00:49:26.046
And those words
