It's his voice you hear on the video.

1451
01:12:11.285 --> 01:12:13.287
Not the voice
of a law enforcement officer.

1452
01:12:25.174 --> 01:12:28.427
Why was Jamal stopped?
He... He doesn't drink.

1453
01:12:29.553 --> 01:12:31.673
We just bought the car.
The brake lights were working.

1454
01:12:31.722 --> 01:12:33.265
- Ma'am...
- He had his registration

1455
01:12:33.349 --> 01:12:34.600
and insurance card with him.

1456
01:12:34.683 --> 01:12:36.310
- I made sure of that.
- Ma'am.

1457
01:12:36.393 --> 01:12:38.604
He wouldn't have given anyone
any reason to stop him.

1458
01:12:38.687 --> 01:12:41.440
No one has said your son was stopped.

1459
01:12:41.523 --> 01:12:44.985
There are at least three individuals
involved in this incident.

1460
01:12:45.736 --> 01:12:49.406
I don't know who was driving the vehicle
when it was pulled over.

1461
01:12:49.490 --> 01:12:50.908
and neither do you.

1462
01:12:52.034 --> 01:12:54.244
You'll cause yourself
a lot less heartache

1463
01:12:54.328 --> 01:12:57.206
if you'll stop jumping to conclusions.

1464
01:12:57.831 --> 01:13:01.418
At the moment... I don't know
why the car was stopped. Okay?

1465
01:13:01.502 --> 01:13:02.378
Okay.

1466
01:13:02.461 --> 01:13:04.922
And right now.
what I've told you is all I know.

1467
01:13:05.005 --> 01:13:05.839
All right.

1468
01:13:05.923 --> 01:13:07.859
As soon as I know anything else.
I'll immediately...

1469
01:13:07.883 --> 01:13:09.134
Fine!

1470
01:13:15.891 --> 01:13:17.434
I will tell you this.

1471
01:13:18.894 --> 01:13:22.564
The car had a bumper sticker on it
that raises some concerns.

1472
01:13:25.442 --> 01:13:27.111
I am aware of that.

1473
01:13:29.238 --> 01:13:32.449
Kind of makes your close scrutiny
of your son's insurance

1474
01:13:32.533 --> 01:13:35.077
and registration card moot.
now doesn't it?

1475
01:13:35.160 --> 01:13:36.412
I don't see how.

1476
01:13:36.495 --> 01:13:38.914
Come on. my sister.
I know you know better than that.

1477
01:13:38.997 --> 01:13:40.332
I am not your sister.

1478
01:13:40.416 --> 01:13:41.875
A black boy in that car

1479
01:13:41.959 --> 01:13:43.544
with a bumper sticker like that?

1480
01:13:43.627 --> 01:13:44.753
He's asking for trouble.

1481
01:13:44.837 --> 01:13:46.505
And what does that tell you?

1482
01:13:46.588 --> 01:13:51.677
It tells me that the world is not the same
for people who look like you and me.

1483
01:13:51.760 --> 01:13:53.262
- Oh. Jesus Christ.
- Yes.

1484
01:13:53.345 --> 01:13:54.763
That's what it tells me.

1485
01:13:54.847 --> 01:13:58.350
And it tells me that the people
who patrol the streets

1486
01:13:58.434 --> 01:14:01.770
with legal authority to use deadly force
are not robots.

1487
01:14:01.854 --> 01:14:04.231
They help their kids
brush their teeth at night

1488
01:14:04.314 --> 01:14:05.899
and read them Dr. Seuss

1489
01:14:05.983 --> 01:14:08.610
and pray they get to do it again
the next night.

1490
01:14:08.694 --> 01:14:12.406
And when they see some nihilistic.
agitating young thug.

1491
01:14:12.489 --> 01:14:14.759
- pride may get the best of them.
- Who do you think you are

1492
01:14:14.783 --> 01:14:15.951
calling my son a thug?

1493
01:14:16.410 --> 01:14:18.745
Running cover for some cracker-ass cop.

1494
01:14:19.955 --> 01:14:20.955
The cop is black.

1495
01:14:22.666 --> 01:14:24.251
The one who made the stop...

1496
01:14:24.334 --> 01:14:25.961
he's black as you and me.

1497
01:14:26.628 --> 01:14:28.255
Let me tell you something. lady.

1498
01:14:28.881 --> 01:14:30.799
I parachuted out of planes.

1499
01:14:30.883 --> 01:14:33.594
I crawled through VC tunnels in Vietnam.

1500
01:14:33.677 --> 01:14:36.930
but the most scared I have ever been
in my life. <i>ever.</i>

1501
01:14:37.473 --> 01:14:40.350
was when I made my first traffic stop
on a ghetto street.

1502
01:14:40.434 --> 01:14:41.434
You know why?

1503
01:14:41.810 --> 01:14:45.397
Because there are hip-hop songs
and bumper stickers

1504
01:14:45.481 --> 01:14:47.441
and mobs shutting down the interstate

1505
01:14:47.524 --> 01:14:49.485
saying that the cops are the enemy.

1506
01:14:49.860 --> 01:14:52.196
So it's okay to challenge them.
it's okay to question them.

1507
01:14:52.279 --> 01:14:54.740
If they pull you over.
it's okay to bust out with an attitude

1508
01:14:54.823 --> 01:14:56.492
and act like gangsters
and have swagger.

1509
01:14:56.575 --> 01:14:59.119
You step up to a cop.
that makes you hard. right?

1510
01:14:59.203 --> 01:15:01.330
Well. all that bullshit gets cops killed.

1511
01:15:01.413 --> 01:15:04.374
I don't know who you're talking about.
but that is not my son.

1512
01:15:04.458 --> 01:15:07.961
My son was taught to be respectful
and assert his rights.

1513
01:15:08.045 --> 01:15:12.633
When I pull you over. you got no grounds
to "assert your rights."

1514
01:15:12.716 --> 01:15:14.760
You know what you got the right to do?

1515
01:15:14.843 --> 01:15:16.929
Shut up and do what I say.

1516
01:15:18.347 --> 01:15:20.557
I can't believe what I'm hearing.

1517
01:15:20.641 --> 01:15:23.894
You serve us. Not the other way around.

1518
01:15:23.977 --> 01:15:27.272
What if your car matches one
in an Amber Alert?

1519
01:15:27.773 --> 01:15:31.401
What if you fit the BOLO of someone
who just shot up a school?

1520
01:15:31.485 --> 01:15:34.821
When you get pulled over.
you got no idea what it might be.

1521
01:15:34.905 --> 01:15:37.407
Some hard-acting fool
just gets in the way.

1522
01:15:37.491 --> 01:15:39.952
Maybe if you'd have grown up
in the Pork 'n' Beans like me.

1523
01:15:40.035 --> 01:15:43.080
you'd understand that black boys
don't act gangsta to be hard.

1524
01:15:44.456 --> 01:15:46.416
They do it to hide their fear.

1525
01:15:46.500 --> 01:15:48.126
I come up in Overtown. lady.

1526
01:15:48.627 --> 01:15:51.171
Ain't nobody got to tell me
why they do what they do.

1527
01:15:51.255 --> 01:15:52.172
But hold up.

1528
01:15:52.256 --> 01:15:55.717
Y'all's family is living
the American Dream. ain't ya?

1529
01:15:56.134 --> 01:15:58.554
Your son got no reason
to be afraid. right?

1530
01:15:58.929 --> 01:16:01.139
Is that what I'm supposed to be doing?

1531
01:16:01.223 --> 01:16:03.475
Teaching him to be scared?

1532
01:16:03.559 --> 01:16:05.561
Be a good boy. keep his mouth shut?

1533
01:16:05.644 --> 01:16:07.062
Damn right.

1534
01:16:07.145 --> 01:16:10.440
And make sure he understands.
that for us...

1535
01:16:10.524 --> 01:16:12.276
there ain't no American Dream.

1536
01:16:14.236 --> 01:16:18.448
Well. I guess I just wasn't raised
to be a bitter Uncle Tom like you.

1537
01:16:19.700 --> 01:16:20.867
Lady. you got a nerve.

1538
01:16:20.951 --> 01:16:22.244
You damn right. I do.

1539
01:16:22.327 --> 01:16:23.829
- I'll tell ya...
- Mm-hmm.

1540
01:16:23.912 --> 01:16:25.330
...two minutes with you.

1541
01:16:25.872 --> 01:16:27.541
and I know your whole adult life.

1542
01:16:27.624 --> 01:16:29.001
- Oh. bullshit.
- No. but I do.

1543
01:16:29.835 --> 01:16:31.545
I know you got a husband

1544
01:16:32.087 --> 01:16:34.673
carries around a picture of you
on his phone.

1545
01:16:34.756 --> 01:16:37.884
and every time he say
some fool-ass racist remark.

1546
01:16:37.968 --> 01:16:39.428
he pull out that picture and go.

1547
01:16:39.511 --> 01:16:42.222
"Oh. no. not me.
'Cause looky here at my black wife."

1548
01:16:43.390 --> 01:16:47.853
I know you could never explain to him
that pain in your heart.

1549
01:16:48.937 --> 01:16:51.273
That pain that claws out your contentment

1550
01:16:51.356 --> 01:16:54.735
because every public service announcement
for hepatitis C

1551
01:16:54.818 --> 01:16:57.571
and every malt liquor billboard
got somebody on it

1552
01:16:57.654 --> 01:16:59.364
look just like your baby boy.

1553
01:17:00.157 --> 01:17:04.995
Or why your son was the tallest
and the smartest kid in third grade.

1554
01:17:05.078 --> 01:17:07.247
but the teacher never seemed
to call on him

1555
01:17:07.331 --> 01:17:10.042
no matter how high
he raised his little brown hand.

1556
01:17:10.125 --> 01:17:14.046
See. 'cause that's a pain
your man could never understand.

1557
01:17:14.129 --> 01:17:17.507
So you tried to kill that pain
by making your son proud

1558
01:17:17.591 --> 01:17:19.718
and telling him to live
the American Dream

1559
01:17:19.801 --> 01:17:22.346
and teaching him to assert his rights.

1560
01:17:22.429 --> 01:17:25.557
instead of teaching him how to survive
as a black man in this country.

1561
01:17:25.641 --> 01:17:26.808
Fuck you!

1562
01:17:28.560 --> 01:17:31.188
One thing I already know for sure
about this incident.

1563
01:17:31.271 --> 01:17:33.523
Just like almost every other one of them.

1564
01:17:34.024 --> 01:17:36.693
if the young brothers
would have just shut their mouths

1565
01:17:36.777 --> 01:17:38.528
and done what they were told.

1566
01:17:38.904 --> 01:17:40.656
none of us would be here tonight.

1567
01:17:41.406 --> 01:17:43.158
which is what I suggest you do.

1568
01:17:44.034 --> 01:17:45.034
Sit tight.

1569
01:17:46.244 --> 01:17:47.244
And shut up.

1570
01:17:49.873 --> 01:17:50.873
And. sister.

1571
01:17:51.291 --> 01:17:53.710
next time you call a black man
an Uncle Tom.

1572
01:17:54.044 --> 01:17:56.171
it'd play a whole lot better
if that black man

1573
01:17:56.254 --> 01:17:59.257
hadn't just dragged your white husband
out the room in handcuffs.

1574
01:18:24.366 --> 01:18:27.285
They booked me.
Gave me a "promise to appear."

1575
01:18:27.369 --> 01:18:28.578
Stupid. Stupid...

1576
01:18:28.662 --> 01:18:30.706
I don't understand this.
I don't understand...

1577
01:18:30.789 --> 01:18:32.791
Why did you walk up to me
at Carl and Joy's party?

1578
01:18:33.542 --> 01:18:34.376
What?

1579
01:18:34.459 --> 01:18:37.379
The first time we ever met.
why did you walk up to me?

1580
01:18:37.462 --> 01:18:38.839
Why did I... oh...

1581
01:18:38.922 --> 01:18:40.924
- Kenny... What? Now?
- Tell me.

1582
01:18:41.007 --> 01:18:43.176
- Tell me again. Please.
- Babe. I...

1583
01:18:45.929 --> 01:18:46.929
Hey.

1584
01:18:49.766 --> 01:18:50.766
Because...

1585
01:18:54.020 --> 01:18:55.522
Because I was staring at you?

1586
01:18:55.605 --> 01:18:57.525
No. I was staring at you.
I couldn't help myself.

1587
01:18:57.566 --> 01:18:58.775
- What else?
- I. um...

1588
01:18:58.859 --> 01:18:59.693
What else?

1589
01:18:59.776 --> 01:19:02.529
You don't think Jamal got himself
into some kind of situation...

1590
01:19:02.654 --> 01:19:05.949
We were standing on Carl and Joy's patio
and we were staring at each other...

1591
01:19:06.032 --> 01:19:07.752
That's right.
We were staring at each other.

1592
01:19:07.826 --> 01:19:09.466
We couldn't take our eyes off each other.

1593
01:19:09.536 --> 01:19:10.912
- And?
- And I...

1594
01:19:11.580 --> 01:19:12.456
walked over.

1595
01:19:12.539 --> 01:19:13.832
You walked over to me.

1596
01:19:13.915 --> 01:19:16.315
And my heart was beating
so fast I could hardly talk.

1597
01:19:16.376 --> 01:19:19.212
And there were all these girls
parading back and forth to the bar.

1598
01:19:19.296 --> 01:19:20.756
but you never looked at one of them.

1599
01:19:20.839 --> 01:19:23.842
You just kept walking and staring at me.

1600
01:19:24.551 --> 01:19:25.969
Yeah.

1601
01:19:26.052 --> 01:19:27.971
- But then you looked up.
- I looked up.

1602
01:19:28.054 --> 01:19:29.097
Right past me.

1603
01:19:29.431 --> 01:19:33.477
And I thought... "Okay. Maybe not."

1604
01:19:33.727 --> 01:19:35.287
- <i>But I...
- But you...</i>

1605
01:19:35.312 --> 01:19:36.912
<i>...put my hand on your shoulder.</i>

1606
01:19:36.980 --> 01:19:38.815
<i>And you pointed out a bird...</i>

1607
01:19:40.317 --> 01:19:41.443
<i>in a tree.</i>

1608
01:19:45.280 --> 01:19:48.408
<i>This gorgeous little red bird.</i>

1609
01:19:48.492 --> 01:19:49.785
<i>And it flew away.</i>

1610
01:19:49.868 --> 01:19:52.204
<i>And you told me it was tired of being...</i>

1611
01:19:52.287 --> 01:19:55.415
<i>The second most beautiful creature
at the party.</i>

1612
01:19:56.750 --> 01:19:59.211
- <i>That's what you said.
- That's right.</i>

1613
01:20:00.462 --> 01:20:02.088
Hey.

1614
01:20:02.798 --> 01:20:04.257
Hey. come here.

1615
01:20:07.260 --> 01:20:09.262
It's okay. It's okay.

1616
01:20:12.849 --> 01:20:14.601
- It's coming apart.
- Mm-mmm.

1617
01:20:14.684 --> 01:20:16.520
Yeah. everything's coming apart.

1618
01:20:17.479 --> 01:20:18.479
Kenny.

1619
01:20:22.192 --> 01:20:23.777
I know you're not coming back.

1620
01:20:28.907 --> 01:20:31.493
It... it hurts. Scott.

1621
01:20:34.120 --> 01:20:35.372
It hurts.

1622
01:20:36.331 --> 01:20:37.958
And the fact that she's white

1623
01:20:38.583 --> 01:20:40.710
makes it almost unbearable.

1624
01:20:45.006 --> 01:20:46.258
I don't love her.

1625
01:20:47.509 --> 01:20:48.593
Oh...

1626
01:20:50.303 --> 01:20:52.055
Then why?

1627
01:20:54.349 --> 01:20:55.349
I just...

1628
01:20:58.311 --> 01:21:00.105
I don't...

1629
01:21:25.922 --> 01:21:28.216
- Kenny. Ken.
- No.

1630
01:21:35.932 --> 01:21:38.560
We made a magnificent person.
didn't we?

1631
01:21:39.060 --> 01:21:40.060
We did.

1632
01:21:42.898 --> 01:21:44.190
I was thinking...

1633
01:21:45.150 --> 01:21:46.359
before you came back.

1634
01:21:46.443 --> 01:21:48.528
about that time
when you and I were fighting...

1635
01:21:48.612 --> 01:21:50.405
I don't even remember what it was about...

1636
01:21:50.488 --> 01:21:54.409
But Jamal was a baby. and I was upset.

1637
01:21:55.201 --> 01:21:58.747
And he thought that I was crying
about the thunder and the lightning...

1638
01:21:58.830 --> 01:22:01.833
- I remember.
- And he said...

1639
01:22:02.542 --> 01:22:04.669
"Don't cry. Mama.

1640
01:22:04.753 --> 01:22:08.173
It's just God taking pictures
of the rain."

1641
01:22:08.256 --> 01:22:10.800
Yeah. We...

1642
01:22:10.884 --> 01:22:13.428
We put it in his baby book.

1643
01:22:13.511 --> 01:22:16.222
And he... He grabbed my tears

1644
01:22:16.848 --> 01:22:21.102
with his itty-bitty hands
and he tried to put them back in my eyes.

1645
01:22:24.314 --> 01:22:25.440
Oh!

1646
01:22:29.611 --> 01:22:31.988
Last night. I told him...

1647
01:22:33.823 --> 01:22:34.823
<i>What?</i>

1648
01:22:37.202 --> 01:22:38.202
What?

1649
01:22:39.996 --> 01:22:42.332
- Ken. Kenny? Kenny.
- No.

1650
01:22:51.049 --> 01:22:57.138
We were both furious.
and he was yelling at me. and... and I...

1651
01:22:57.597 --> 01:22:59.891
- You what?
- I said things to him.

1652
01:22:59.975 --> 01:23:00.976
Okay. What things?

1653
01:23:01.059 --> 01:23:03.061
- Oh. God.
- Kendra. Hey. hey.

1654
01:23:03.812 --> 01:23:05.021
- Ken...
- Horrible...

1655
01:23:05.605 --> 01:23:06.439
Hey.

1656
01:23:06.523 --> 01:23:07.523
...ugly...

1657
01:23:10.568 --> 01:23:13.238
things a mother
should never say to a child.

1658
01:23:13.321 --> 01:23:14.489
- Okay.
- Oh. God.

1659
01:23:19.244 --> 01:23:21.705
I just wanna hold him.

1660
01:23:25.166 --> 01:23:28.586
I wanna look him in the eyes
and I just wanna...

1661
01:23:28.670 --> 01:23:31.464
I wanna take every word I said
out of his head

1662
01:23:31.548 --> 01:23:33.383
and bury it in the ground.

1663
01:23:33.466 --> 01:23:35.593
- It's okay.
- God damn it! "Shoot cops."

1664
01:23:41.391 --> 01:23:45.353
I should... I should have
gone out there with a razor

1665
01:23:45.437 --> 01:23:47.939
and peeled that goddamn thing
off his car.

1666
01:23:48.023 --> 01:23:48.857
No.

1667
01:23:48.940 --> 01:23:50.859
I should've gone out there
as soon as I saw it.

1668
01:23:50.942 --> 01:23:52.586
Shouldn't matter.
shouldn't make a difference.

1669
01:23:52.610 --> 01:23:54.654
It's not your fault. It's not his fault.

1670
01:23:54.738 --> 01:23:57.866
I'll never say a cross word to him again.
I just need to know he's okay.

1671
01:23:57.949 --> 01:23:59.159
He is. He's okay.

1672
01:23:59.242 --> 01:24:01.042
- Please. Jesus. let him be okay.
- He's okay.

1673
01:24:01.536 --> 01:24:02.536
He's okay.

1674
01:24:05.165 --> 01:24:06.916
He's okay.

1675
01:24:18.428 --> 01:24:23.475
Your son. Jamal Connor.
was a rear seat passenger

1676
01:24:23.558 --> 01:24:26.686
in a vehicle with a Jarvis Bell

1677
01:24:26.770 --> 01:24:28.396
and a DeShawn Rolle.

1678
01:24:29.147 --> 01:24:32.400
Bell was wanted on a misdemeanor warrant
for marijuana possession.

1679
01:24:33.651 --> 01:24:36.154
The car was tailed by a Metro cruiser

1680
01:24:36.237 --> 01:24:38.865
near the Scott Projects in Liberty City.

1681
01:24:38.948 --> 01:24:42.744
where the driver was observed
purchasing a nickel bag of marijuana.

1682
01:24:42.827 --> 01:24:43.703
God damn it.

1683
01:24:43.787 --> 01:24:48.124
Following the purchase.
while driving westbound on 79th Street.

1684
01:24:48.208 --> 01:24:50.794
the car was approached
by a marked patrol car.

1685
01:24:50.877 --> 01:24:54.672
Officer Rodney Banks.
who had witnessed the purchase.

1686
01:24:54.756 --> 01:24:55.924
<i>pulled the car over.</i>

1687
01:24:57.050 --> 01:24:58.968
The camera on the patrol car

1688
01:24:59.052 --> 01:25:02.639
shows Officer Banks approaching
the driver's side of the vehicle.

1689
01:25:03.306 --> 01:25:05.517
Mr. Bell was driving the car.

1690
01:25:06.684 --> 01:25:10.563
The officer returns to his vehicle
with the occupants' identification

1691
01:25:10.647 --> 01:25:14.067
and apparently begins checking them
on his laptop.

1692
01:25:14.692 --> 01:25:20.115
